<TITLE> 6 reported drowned in Dhaka water bodies </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 29 (bdnews24.com)  Six people, including two medical students, drowned in three separate incidents in Dhaka on Wednesday, police said. The drowned students were identified as Abdul Al Mahmud Rubel and Meraj Khandaker Raju of Salimullah Medical College. "Rubel's body was recovered in Banshi pond in Dhamrai at about 5pm. Raju's body has not yet been recovered," Dhamrai police chief, Alamgir Hossain told bdnews24.com at 9pm. "The two students went missing after going to the pond for a swim around 1:30pm," Dr Mohammad Jahurul Haque at Dhamrai Hospital told bdnews24.com. A total of 20-22 students of the medical college were staying at Dhamrai Health Complex as part of a seven-day field trip, Haque said. Another two people, including a young boy, drowned as their boat capsized in a beel, an open water body, near the Turag River in the capital. The dead were identified as 12-year old Ronnie, who was plying the small country boat, and a passenger, local madrasah teacher Abdul Aziz, aged 50, Turag police chief Khandaker Rezaul Hasan told bdnews24.com. In a separate incident, two youths drowned in a beel adjacent to the flood barrier at Hazaribagh as they were being chased by police, Kamrangirchar police chief Nazrul Islam told bdnews24.com. Police identified the youths as Jibon, 18, and Sani, 17, and said they drowned in the beel as police gave chase to a gang was allegedly trying to grab a house in the locality. Police arrested nine people at the spot while others escaped, Islam said. Neither body was recovered yet, he added. b
